<div id="review_114374270" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/114374270" />
    <a title="Jesse Field" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3633038-jesse-field"><img alt="Jesse Field" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1273174024p2/3633038.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/114374270?book_show_action=true">Jul 30, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jesse Field" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jesse Field" href="/user/show/3633038-jesse-field">Jesse Field</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer114374270" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10950482689901524628">This is the kind of book that, when read carefully, can transform the English reader from perfect ignorance of Chinese culture to nerd-like engagement with aesthetics, society, history, mythology, folklore, science, medicine, technology, and the list goes on and on. It&apos;s really worth remembering how powerful a single book can be, and if you think about the variety and range of this book, you begin to understand why Chinese writing so often comes in anthologies and collections.<br/><br/>I&apos;ll likely return </span>
  <span id="freeText10950482689901524628" style="display:none">This is the kind of book that, when read carefully, can transform the English reader from perfect ignorance of Chinese culture to nerd-like engagement with aesthetics, society, history, mythology, folklore, science, medicine, technology, and the list goes on and on. It's really worth remembering how powerful a single book can be, and if you think about the variety and range of this book, you begin to understand why Chinese writing so often comes in anthologies and collections.<br /><br />I'll likely return to this book again and again, both for personal benefit and to assign to my students. Just today I re-read the story "<a href="http://wandermonkey.blogspot.com/2010/07/note-pu-songlings-twenty-years-dream.html" rel="nofollow noopener">Twenty Years a Dream"</a> (Pu Songling's original title was "Locket" 连锁, which is the name of the ghost girl). </span>
  <a data-text-id="10950482689901524628" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


