    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2689655372" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2689655372" />
    <a title="Inkspill" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/79575646-inkspill"><img alt="Inkspill" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615973746p2/79575646.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2689655372?book_show_action=true">Mar 01, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Inkspill" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Inkspill" href="/user/show/79575646-inkspill">Inkspill</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79575646-inkspill?shelf=fiction-comical-edge-or-fun-reads">fiction-comical-edge-or-fun-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/79575646-inkspill?shelf=myths-old-stories-or-folklore">myths-old-stories-or-folklore</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2689655372" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3882628388594338640">Reading <i>Strange Tales</i> came as a complete surprise to me, a really one, these are deliciously enchanting tales, full of wit and written with a light hand.<br/><br/>This Penguin edition has 104 of the 550+ of these tales available in 2 volumes on Gutenberg, translated by <i>Herbert A Giles</i>. The bookish in me compared the 2 translations between some tales, and I gotta say this Mitford one I connected to all the subtleties of drama and charm better. Mitford, in his own intro has a lot of respect for Giles’ trans</span>
  <span id="freeText3882628388594338640" style="display:none">Reading <i>Strange Tales</i> came as a complete surprise to me, a really one, these are deliciously enchanting tales, full of wit and written with a light hand.<br /><br />This Penguin edition has 104 of the 550+ of these tales available in 2 volumes on Gutenberg, translated by <i>Herbert A Giles</i>. The bookish in me compared the 2 translations between some tales, and I gotta say this Mitford one I connected to all the subtleties of drama and charm better. Mitford, in his own intro has a lot of respect for Giles’ translation and also notes that Songling wrote in a complicated structure of the Chinese language which today’s readers of lit in the Chinese language would find challenging. Mitford adds, that his high brow writing was for a limited audience, his educated friends, I got the sense that he did this as they would appreciate the handling of the Chinese language to bring out the aesthetics and humour in these stories but with a light touch.<br /><br />IMHO, in comparing these translations Miford brings out the subtle tones and nuances he says are in Songling’s work, Giles translation was for an audience of another time which to my modern eyes are not as smooth in reading as Mitford’s.<br /><br />The stories in this collection are of varying length and a mix of supernatural and naturalistic genres, further blended by types and themes. It’s a heady mix of relationships: love, moral lesson, sex, family and friendship; made more so when humans and spirits exist on the same plateau bringing in an edge of surreal, and at times absurd, to my modern eyes without dampening the charm of these stories. And if that’s not enough then a good portion of them are presented as accounts witnessed first-hand, some by Songling’s friends, others are recorded in history.<br /><br />The big wonderful surprise for me in this edition were lithographs which accompany most of these 104 stories which depict a moment. Along with this and the intro, there is a pronunciation guide, notes at the back and a translation of Songling’s preface.<br /><br />It’s good to have this on my kindle, now whenever I am looking for a light, short read I can go to this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3882628388594338640" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

