<div id="review_617446141" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/617446141" />
    <a title="Mizuki" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16842102-mizuki"><img alt="Mizuki" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1368277474p2/16842102.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/617446141?book_show_action=true">May 16, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mizuki" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mizuki" href="/user/show/16842102-mizuki">Mizuki</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" 9781421248554" href="/book/show/1560599.Strange_Stories_From_A_Chinese_Studio">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer617446141" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7689775897967246333">It is a book I read as a child, and many of the famous tales from <i>Strange Stories From A Chinese Studio</i> still stay in my mind, always.<br/><br/>Pu Songling created an exquisite, imaginative fantasy world based faithfully and richly on the traditional Chinese myths and folklore. It is a world inhabited by gods, ghosts, demons, magical animals and humans. <br/><br/>In one of the tales, a man fell in love with a beautiful maiden painted on the wall of an ancient temple; in another tale, a man put on a magical robe and</span>
  <span id="freeText7689775897967246333" style="display:none">It is a book I read as a child, and many of the famous tales from <i>Strange Stories From A Chinese Studio</i> still stay in my mind, always.<br /><br />Pu Songling created an exquisite, imaginative fantasy world based faithfully and richly on the traditional Chinese myths and folklore. It is a world inhabited by gods, ghosts, demons, magical animals and humans. <br /><br />In one of the tales, a man fell in love with a beautiful maiden painted on the wall of an ancient temple; in another tale, a man put on a magical robe and shapeshifted into a raven and lived a far happier life than the old life he had as a mortal. There are many, many more for readers to discover.<br /><br />There are romance, comedies, moral tales as well as thrillers among the Strange Stories. I'd recommend everyone to try this remarkable book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7689775897967246333" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

