<div id="review_1147568258" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1147568258" />
    <a title="Laurie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26553024-laurie"><img alt="Laurie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1623871223p2/26553024.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1147568258?book_show_action=true">Apr 25, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laurie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laurie" href="/user/show/26553024-laurie">Laurie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=china">china</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=medieval-period">medieval-period</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=musings">musings</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=social-history">social-history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=taoism">taoism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26553024-laurie?shelf=china-literature">china-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1147568258" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1058131989628572555">Sublime. With every story I read I found myself immersed in the rich life and thought of Ming dynasty China. Here we meet fox spirits, Taoist monks versed in the art of alchemy, magic implements, beautiful women possessed by the ghosts of the recently departed and vexed lovers. Unlike ghost stories in the western tradition, these tales are designed to engage, entertain and enlighten the reader; not scare us. Short tales contain get depth of insight into the human condition and psychology. Minfor</span>
  <span id="freeText1058131989628572555" style="display:none">Sublime. With every story I read I found myself immersed in the rich life and thought of Ming dynasty China. Here we meet fox spirits, Taoist monks versed in the art of alchemy, magic implements, beautiful women possessed by the ghosts of the recently departed and vexed lovers. Unlike ghost stories in the western tradition, these tales are designed to engage, entertain and enlighten the reader; not scare us. Short tales contain get depth of insight into the human condition and psychology. Minford's deft translation of the 104 (of an original 500) tales reads with a clarity and cadence that must surely reflect the beauty of classical Chinese. Illustrations, an outstanding introduction by the translator, glossary, bibliography and extensive background notes on most tales add to fullness of the reading experience.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1058131989628572555" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


